---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
import { agents } from '../data/agents';
---

<Base title="About">
  <section class="hero" style="padding-top: 56px;">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>About <span class="grad">AI Agents Hub</span></h1>
      <p>An independent, hand-curated directory of AI agents worth knowing about.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container" style="max-width: 720px;">
      <div class="prose">
        <h2>Why this exists</h2>
        <p>
          The AI agent landscape is moving fast — too fast for anyone to keep track of by hand.
          Existing directories are either overwhelming (thousands of entries, no signal) or
          promotional (every tool is "the best"). This site aims for the middle ground:
          a tight, opinionated list of {agents.length} agents with honest notes on each.
        </p>

        <h2>How we pick</h2>
        <p>Every agent here has to clear a bar:</p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Real traction</strong> — active development and a genuine user base.</li>
          <li><strong>Clear use case</strong> — you should know what it's for in one sentence.</li>
          <li><strong>Accessible</strong> — you can actually try it, not just watch a demo.</li>
          <li><strong>Distinct</strong> — it does something the others in its category don't.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>What the badges mean</h2>
        <p>
          <span class="badge oss">Open Source</span> — code is public and self-hostable. &nbsp;
          <span class="badge commercial">Commercial</span> — paid product, often closed-source. &nbsp;
          <span class="badge freemium">Freemium</span> — free tier with paid upgrades.
        </p>

        <h2>Independence</h2>
        <p>
          This is an independent project. Listings are not paid placements. If that ever changes,
          it will be disclosed clearly on the listing itself.
        </p>

        <h2>Suggest an agent</h2>
        <p>
          Spotted an agent we're missing? Found something outdated? The cleanest way is to
          open an issue or pull request on the source repository. Every listing is just a
          data file — easy to add or fix.
        </p>

        <div class="verdict-box" style="margin-top: 32px;">
          <div class="label">Note</div>
          <p style="margin: 0; color: var(--text);">
            AI Agents Hub is an independent directory. All product names, logos, and brands
            are property of their respective owners.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
